## User Story
As a **developer**,
I want **a properly structured monorepo with all required packages**,
So that **I can develop frontend, backend, and solver in a coordinated way**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status |
|----|----------|--------|
| AC1 | Monorepo structure with apps/web, apps/api, solver/ exists | PASS |
| AC2 | `bun install` succeeds without errors | PASS |
| AC3 | TypeScript compilation passes for all packages | PASS |
| AC4 | Docker Compose configuration exists | PASS |

## Implementation Details

### Files Created
- `package.json` - Workspaces configuration with bun
- `apps/web/` - Next.js 14 App Router application
- `apps/api/` - Fastify 4 backend server
- `apps/solver/` - Python FastAPI with OR-Tools
- `packages/types/` - Shared TypeScript types
- `docker-compose.yml` - PostgreSQL and Redis services

### Technical Decisions
- Used Bun as package manager for speed
- Next.js 14 with App Router for modern React patterns
- Fastify 4 for high-performance API
- Drizzle ORM for type-safe database access

## Dev Notes
Story completed as part of initial infrastructure setup. No blockers encountered.
